characters.description: A traveler from another world who had their only kin taken away, forcing them to embark on a journey to find The Seven.

talents.weeklyBossDrop: The Cornerstone of Stars and Flames

characters.name: Jean
characters.title: Dandelion Knight
characters.description: The righteous and rigorous Dandelion Knight, and Acting Grand Master of Mondstadt's Knights of Favonius.

characters.name: Lisa
characters.title: Witch of Purple Rose
characters.description: The languid but knowledgeable Librarian of the Knights of Favonius, deemed by Sumeru Akademiya to be their most distinguished graduate in the past two centuries.

characters.name: Barbara
characters.title: Shining Idol
characters.description: Every citizen of Mondstadt adores Barbara. She learned the word "idol" from a magazine.

characters.name: Kaeya
characters.title: Frostwind Swordsman
characters.description: An accomplished swordsman and a strategic thinker in the Knights of Favonius, rumored to hail from beyond Mondstadt.

characters.name: Diluc
characters.title: Dark Side of Dawn
characters.description: The tycoon of a winery empire in Mondstadt, unmatched in every possible way.

characters.name: Razor
characters.title: Wolf Boy
characters.description: A boy who lives among the wolves in Wolvendom of Mondstadt, away from human civilization. As agile as lightning.

characters.name: Amber
characters.title: Gliding Champion
characters.description: Always energetic and full of life, Amber's the best — albeit only — Outrider of the Knights of Favonius.

characters.name: Venti
characters.title: Windborne Bard
characters.description: One of the many bards of Mondstadt, who freely wanders the city's streets and alleys.

characters.name: Xiangling
characters.title: Exquisite Delicacy
characters.description: A renowned chef from Liyue. She's extremely passionate about cooking and excels at making her signature hot and spicy dishes.

characters.name: Beidou
characters.title: Uncrowned Lord of the Ocean
characters.description: Captain of her crew, The Crux. She's quite an unbound and forthright woman.

characters.name: Xingqiu
characters.title: Juvenile Galant
characters.description: A young man carrying a longsword who is frequently seen at book booths. He has a chivalrous heart and yearns for justice and fairness for all.

characters.name: Ningguang
characters.title: Eclipsing Star
characters.description: The Tianquan of the Liyue Qixing. Her wealth is unsurpassed in all of Teyvat.

characters.name: Klee
characters.title: Fleeing Sunlight
characters.description: An explosives expert and a regular at the Knights of Favonius's confinement room. Also known as Fleeing Sunlight.

characters.name: Fischl
characters.title: Prinzessin der Verurteilung!
characters.description: A mysterious girl who calls herself "Prinzessin der Verurteilung" and travels with a night raven named Oz.

characters.name: Bennett
characters.title: Trial by Fire
characters.description: A good-natured adventurer from Mondstadt who's unfortunately extremely unlucky.

characters.name: Noelle
characters.title: Chivalric Blossom
characters.description: A maid who faithfully serves the Knights of Favonius. She dreams of joining their ranks someday.

characters.name: Qiqi
characters.title: Icy Resurrection
characters.description: An apprentice and herb gatherer at Bubu Pharmacy. An undead with a bone-white complexion, she seldom has much in the way of words or emotion.

characters.name: Chongyun
characters.title: Frozen Ardor
characters.description: A young exorcist from a family of exorcists. He does everything he can to suppress his abundance of yang energy.

characters.name: Mona
characters.title: Astral Reflection
characters.description: A mysterious young astrologer who proclaims herself to be "Astrologist Mona Megistus," and who possesses abilities to match the title. Erudite, but prideful.

characters.name: Keqing
characters.title: Driving Thunder
characters.description: The Yuheng of the Liyue Qixing. Keqing has much to say about Rex Lapis's unilateral approach to policymaking in Liyue — but in truth, gods admire skeptics such as her quite a lot.

characters.name: Sucrose
characters.title: Harmless Sweetie
characters.description: An alchemist filled with curiosity about all things. She researches bio-alchemy.

characters.name: Zhongli
characters.title: Vago Mundo
characters.description: A mysterious expert contracted by the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. Extremely knowledgeable in all things.

characters.name: Tartaglia
characters.title: Childe
characters.description: No. 11 of The Harbingers, also known as "Childe." His name is highly feared on the battlefield.

characters.name: Diona
characters.title: Kätzlein Cocktail
characters.description: A young lady who has inherited trace amounts of non-human blood. She is the incredibly popular bartender of the Cat's Tail tavern.

characters.name: Xinyan
characters.title: Blazing Riff
characters.description: Liyue's sole rock 'n' roll musician. She rebels against ossified prejudices using her music and passionate singing.

characters.name: Ganyu
characters.title: Plenilune Gaze
characters.description: The secretary at Yuehai Pavilion. The blood of the qilin, an illuminated beast, flows within her veins.

characters.name: Albedo
characters.title: Kreideprinz
characters.description: A genius known as the Kreideprinz, he is the Chief Alchemist and Captain of the Investigation Team of the Knights of Favonius.

characters.name: Xiao
characters.title: Vigilant Yaksha
characters.description: A yaksha adeptus who defends Liyue. Also heralded as the "Conqueror of Demons" and "Vigilant Yaksha."

characters.name: Hu Tao
characters.title: Fragrance in Thaw
characters.description: The 77th Director of the Wangsheng Funeral Parlor. She took over the business at a rather young age.

characters.name: Rosaria
characters.title: Thorny Benevolence
characters.description: A sister of the church, though you wouldn't know it if it weren't for her attire. Known for her sharp, cold words and manner, she often works alone.

characters.name: Yanfei
characters.title: Wise Innocence
characters.description: A well-known legal adviser active in Liyue Harbor. A brilliant young lady in whose veins runs the blood of an illuminated beast.

characters.name: Eula
characters.title: Dance of the Shimmering Wave
characters.description: The Spindrift Knight, a scion of the old aristocracy, and the Captain of the Knights of Favonius Reconnaissance Company. The reason for which a descendant of the ancient nobles might join the Knights remains a great mystery in Mondstadt to this very day.

characters.name: Kaedehara Kazuha
characters.title: Scarlet Leaves Pursue Wild Waves
characters.description: A wandering samurai from Inazuma who is currently with Liyue's Crux Fleet. A gentle and carefree soul whose heart hides a great many burdens from the past.

characters.name: Kamisato Ayaka
characters.title: Frostflake Heron
characters.description: Daughter of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Dignified and elegant, as well as wise and strong.

characters.name: Yoimiya
characters.title: Frolicking Flames
characters.description: Owner of Naganohara Fireworks. Known as the "Queen of the Summer Festival," she excels in her craft of creating fireworks that symbolize people's hopes and dreams.

characters.name: Sayu
characters.title: Mujina Ninja
characters.description: A pint-sized ninja attached to the Shuumatsuban, who always seems to be lacking sleep.

characters.name: Raiden Shogun
characters.title: Plane of Euthymia
characters.description: Her Excellency, the Almighty Narukami Ogosho, who promised the people of Inazuma an unchanging Eternity.

characters.name: Sangonomiya Kokomi
characters.title: Pearl of Wisdom
characters.description: The Divine Priestess of Watatsumi Island. All of the island's affairs are at this young lady's fingertips.

characters.name: Kujou Sara
characters.title: Crowfeather Kaburaya
characters.description: A general of the Tenryou Commission. Bold, decisive, and skilled in battle.

characters.name: Aloy
characters.title: Savior From Another World
characters.description: Formerly an outcast, now a hunter of unparalleled skill. Ready to do the right thing at any time.

characters.name: Thoma
characters.title: Protector From Afar
characters.description: The Kamisato Clan's housekeeper. A well-known "fixer" in Inazuma.

characters.name: Gorou
characters.title: Canine Warrior
characters.description: The great general of Watatsumi Island's forces. He is deeply trusted by his subordinates.

characters.name: Arataki Itto
characters.title: Hanamizaka Heroics
characters.description: The first and greatest head of the Arataki Gang, famed throughout Inazuma City's Hanamizaka... Wait, what? You've never heard of them? Are you trying to be funny here?

characters.name: Shenhe
characters.title: Lonesome Transcendence
characters.description: An adepti disciple with a most unusual air about her. Having spent much time cultivating in isolation in Liyue's mountains, she has become every bit as cool and distant as the adepti themselves.

characters.name: Yun Jin
characters.title: Stage Lucida
characters.description: A renowned Liyue opera singer who is skilled in both playwriting and singing. Her style is one-of-a-kind, exquisite and delicate, much like the person herself.

characters.name: Yae Miko
characters.title: Astute Amusement
characters.description: Lady Guuji of the Grand Narukami Shrine. Also serves as the editor-in-chief of Yae Publishing House. Unimaginable intelligence and cunning are hidden under her beautiful appearance.

characters.name: Kamisato Ayato
characters.title: Pillar of Fortitude
characters.description: The young but highly accomplished head of the Yashiro Commission's Kamisato Clan. Cultured and polite, he is a man of many ways and means.

characters.name: Yelan
characters.title: Valley Orchid
characters.description: A mysterious person who claims to work for the Ministry of Civil Affairs, but is a "non-entity" on the Ministry of Civil Affairs' list.

characters.name: Kuki Shinobu
characters.title: Mender of Tribulations
characters.description: The capable and reliable Arataki Gang deputy leader - Please note: capable and reliable are not appellations for the "Arataki Gang," but for their deputy leader in specific.

characters.name: Shikanoin Heizou
characters.title: Analytical Harmony
characters.description: A young prodigy detective from the Tenryou Commission. His senses are sharp and his thoughts are clear.

characters.name: Collei
characters.title: Sprout of Rebirth
characters.description: A trainee ranger active in Avidya Forest. Behind her enthusiastic words and actions hides a slightly introverted personality.

characters.name: Dori
characters.title: Treasure of Dream Garden
characters.description: An elusive merchant who has a fondness for glittering Mora.

characters.name: Tighnari
characters.title: Verdant Strider
characters.description: A young researcher well-versed in botany who currently serves as a Forest Watcher in Avidya Forest. He is a straight shooter with a warm heart — and a dab hand at guiding even the dullest of pupils.

characters.name: Nilou
characters.title: Dance of Lotuslight
characters.description: The star of the Zubayr Theater. She is full of warmth and innocence, and her dances are lively and elegant.

characters.name: Cyno
characters.title: Judicator of Secrets
characters.description: The General Mahamatra in charge of supervising the researchers of the Akademiya. It is said that when he gets down to work, the General Mahamatra is even more efficient than the "Great Vayuvyastra" made by the Kshahrewar.

characters.name: Candace
characters.title: Golden Vow
characters.description: A descendant of King Deshret with an amber left eye. The defender of Aaru Village.

characters.name: Nahida
characters.title: Physic of Purity
characters.description: A caged bird secluded within the confines of the Sanctuary of Surasthana who can only see the world in her dreams.

characters.name: Layla
characters.title: Fantastical Evening Star
characters.description: A Rtawahist student who specializes in Theoretical Astrology. Heavily prone to somnambulism and locked in a grinding war with sleep deprivation, the problem of restful slumber is a most troubling one to her.

characters.name: Wanderer
characters.title: Eons Adrift
characters.description: A wayfaring figure whose identity is a mystery. He dresses like a mountain ascetic, but he certainly does not act the part.

characters.name: Faruzan
characters.title: Enigmatic Machinist
characters.description: A researcher from "one hundred years ago." She enjoys self-identifying as everyone's senior, and has significant knowledge of ancient scripts and machines of all kinds.

characters.name: Yaoyao
characters.title: Burgeoning Grace
characters.description: Streetward Rambler's youngest disciple. A gentle and caring "little adult."

characters.name: Alhaitham
characters.title: Admonishing Instruction
characters.description: The current scribe of the Sumeru Akademiya, a man endowed with extraordinary intelligence and talent. He lives free — free from the searching eyes of ordinary people, anyway.

characters.name: Dehya
characters.title: Flame-Mane
characters.description: A member of the Eremites, a mercenary organization that roams the sands of Sumeru. Valiant and powerful, she enjoys great fame amongst her fellow Eremites.

characters.name: Mika
characters.title: Coordinates of Clear Frost
characters.description: A young knight born to an ordinary family. He serves as a Front-Line Surveyor in his Company. He is a low-key and cautious character.

characters.name: Kaveh
characters.title: Empyrean Reflection
characters.description: A renowned architect from Sumeru who perhaps cares a bit too much about too many things. He is an aesthete troubled by reality.

characters.name: Baizhu
characters.title: Beyond Mortality
characters.description: The owner of Bubu Pharmacy, who is rarely seen without the white snake named Changsheng. His medicinal knowledge is encyclopedic, and his personal intrigues subtle.

characters.name: Kirara
characters.title: Cat Upon the Eaves
characters.description: A courier for Komaniya Express, a delivery company in Inazuma. A nekomata who loves her job and human society.

characters.name: Lynette
characters.title: Elegance in the Shadows
characters.description: A magic assistant of few words, her emotions are as inscrutable as any cat's.

characters.name: Lyney
characters.title: Spectacle of Phantasmagoria
characters.description: A famed Fontainian magician who possesses great stage presence as well as gift of the gab. Audiences are enthralled by his exquisite skills, and they hang on to his every clever word.

characters.name: Freminet
characters.title: Yearning for Unseen Depths
characters.description: A reserved young man who is well-versed in diving. Beneath his distant, icy demeanor lies a pure heart bereft of all flaws.

characters.name: Wriothesley
characters.title: Emissary of Solitary Iniquity
characters.description: Duke of the Fortress of Meropide, Lord Incognito of the murky depths.

characters.name: Neuvillette
characters.title: Ordainer of Inexorable Judgment
characters.description: The Chief Justice of Fontaine, known as the Iudex, is renowned for his unassailable impartiality.

characters.name: Charlotte
characters.title: Lens of Verity
characters.description: Indefatigable reporter of The Steambird, constantly on the hunt for the "truth."

characters.name: Furina
characters.title: Endless Solo of Solitude
characters.description: The absolute focus of the stage of judgment, until the final applause sounds.

characters.name: Chevreuse
characters.title: Executor of Justice
characters.description: The captain of the Special Security and Surveillance Patrol, who wears justice as an ever-present seal upon her heart. Her musket shall only ever point at the guilty.

characters.name: Navia
characters.title: Helm of the Radiant Rose
characters.description: The current President of Spina di Rosula, who is lovely, dutiful, and a great boss.

characters.name: Gaming
characters.title: Leonine Vanguard
characters.description: Guard of the Sword and Strongbox Secure Transport Agency, and the head of the "Mighty Mythical Beasts" Wushou troupe.

characters.name: Xianyun
characters.title: Passerine Herald
characters.description: One of the Mighty and Illuminated Adepti of Jueyun, known as "Cloud Retainer." Expert in all kinds of mechanical contraptions, her heart now turns towards the affairs of the mortal world, through which she walks under the name "Xianyun."

characters.name: Chiori
characters.title: The Thundering Seamstress
characters.description: The owner of Chioriya Boutique. A tailor renowned throughout Fontaine.

characters.name: Arlecchino
characters.title: Dire Balemoon
characters.description: "The Knave," Fourth of the Fatui Harbingers. A poised, ruthless diplomat. To the children in the House of the Hearth, she is their feared yet dependable "Father."

characters.name: Sigewinne
characters.title: Wondrous Dragonheir
characters.description: A Melusine and the Fortress of Meropide's head nurse. She cares equally for every convict locked in the undersea prison.

characters.name: Sethos
characters.title: Wisdom's Measure
characters.description: The Temple of Silence's heir. Burdened with secrets, he comes from the sands.

characters.name: Clorinde
characters.title: Candlebearer, Shadowhunter
characters.description: An undefeated Champion Duelist. Sword in hand, she defends justice in the Court of Fontaine.

characters.name: Emilie
characters.title: A Thousand Scents Traced
characters.description: A Fontainian perfumer, one who bottles secrets.

characters.name: Kachina
characters.title: Mottled Gold Yet Unsmelted
characters.description: A young warrior of the Nanatzcayan, given the Ancient Name of "Uthabiti." Kind-hearted and insatiably persistent, she grows stronger and more capable with each setback she faces.

characters.name: Kinich
characters.title: Turnfire Hunt
characters.description: A Huitztlan Saurian Hunter skilled at counting costs.

characters.name: Mualani
characters.title: Splish-Splash Wavechaser
characters.description: A well-known guide in Natlan who owns a watersports shop, and expert in all forms of wave-chasing.

characters.name: Xilonen
characters.title: Ardent Flames Forge the Soul
characters.description: A Name Engraver of the Nanatzcayan, she is especially skilled at finding a good balance between the heavy responsibilities of her job and living well.

characters.name: Chasca
characters.title: Skyborne Arbiter
characters.description: The Peacemaker of the Tlalocan, the ender of all disputes.

characters.name: Ororon
characters.title: Shadow of the Night-Wind
characters.description: A young man from the Masters of the Night-Wind who instead lives in the wild alongside all manner of life.

characters.name: Mavuika
characters.title: Night-Igniting Flame
characters.description: The leader of Natlan who inherited the Ancient Name of "Kiongozi." She made a vow to illuminate the future of the nation of war with the Sacred Flame.

characters.name: Citlali
characters.title: Obsidian Opalstar
characters.description: The great shaman from the Masters of the Night-Wind, the universally-revered Granny Itztli.

characters.name: Lan Yan
characters.title: Spring Woven From Jade
characters.description: A rattan weaver from Chenyu Vale. Clear-minded and well-tempered, she is as lively as a mountain spring.

characters.name: Yumemizuki Mizuki
characters.title: Embrace of Enchanting Dreams
characters.description: A shareholder of Aisa Bathhouse, a baku, and a clinical psychologist. Dedicated to the dispersal of nightmares, and to bringing people peace of mind.

characters.name: Iansan
characters.title: Tempered in Molten Stone
characters.description: Head coach of the fitness club at the Collective of Plenty, and a renowned Natlanese nutritionist.

characters.name: Varesa
characters.title: Strength in Serenity
characters.description: A laid-back orchard manager and warrior of the Collective of Plenty. An aspiring hero who hungers for justice... and lots and lots of food!

characters.name: Escoffier
characters.title: Tasteful Excellence
characters.description: The ex-head chef of Hotel Debord, renowned throughout Fontaine as the Patissiere Supreme and vanguard of precision gastronomy. Has incomparably strict standards when it comes to cooking.

characters.name: Ifa
characters.title: In the Wake of Wandering Winds
characters.description: A vet from the Flower-Feather Clan who cherishes the life he leads alongside all manner of living things — people, animals, you name it.
